<p>Last week as I was spending a glorious day in the countryside of Provence with a new friend and my French family (who my family has known for 50 years), I felt immensely at peace and content. The specter of reconfinement was looming but I was ignoring it. I combined a little list of the things that were making me happy in that moment and in the last few days to remember this special time and to remind myself of the good stuff to look forward to when reconfinement is over. I called this list â€˜petits instances de bonheur.â€™</p>

